The article is a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on June 15, 2018, in honor of Father's Day. The proclamation pays tribute to fathers and their role in supporting and caring for their loved ones. It emphasizes the importance of fathers as role models who instill values of hard work and dedication in their children. The proclamation also highlights the positive impact of active fatherhood on children's lives, both emotionally and economically. The President calls on government officials to display the flag of the United States on all government buildings on Father's Day and encourages state and local governments, as well as the people of the United States, to observe Father's Day with appropriate ceremonies.